In this section a discussion was presented on the handover process in \gls<<1403>>gsm<<1403>> network. The effect this has on channel selected as well as the different handover procedures was highlighted. 
\section<<1404>>Summary<<1404>>
In this chapter a broad discussion was given of modern cellular technology, specifically \gls<<1405>>gsm<<1405>> cellular network technology. A brief history on how \gls<<1406>>gsm<<1406>> was developed to be the most widely used cellular technology in use today was provided. The \gls<<1407>>gsm<<1407>> architecture components followed. In the \gls<<1408>>gsm<<1408>> architecture all the network components present in a modern \gls<<1409>>gsm<<1409>> network were identified.
\begin<<1495>>tex2html_deferred<<1495>>\par\end<<1496>>tex2html_deferred<<1496>>
Following the discussion of the \gls<<1410>>gsm<<1410>> network components, a broad overview was given of the communication interfaces used between the \gls<<1411>>gsm<<1411>> network components to communicate with each other. This was followed by a definition of the \gls<<1412>>gsm<<1412>> channels which are used on the interfaces to communicate information.
\begin<<1497>>tex2html_deferred<<1497>>\par\end<<1498>>tex2html_deferred<<1498>>
The chapter concluded with the handover process which is used to allow an \gls<<1413>>MS<<1413>> device to move freely geographically within the network. 
